      "note": "Or: \"guides whom He wills onto a straight way\". As regards the expression salam, rendered here and in many other places as \"peace\" and elsewhere as \"salvation\", see surah 5, note 29. It is obvious that the term dar as-salam (\"abode of peace\") denotes not only the condition of ultimate happiness in the hereafter - alluded to in the allegory of paradise - but also the spiritual condition of a true believer in this world: namely, a state of inner security, of peace with God, with one's natural environment, and within oneself."
